Perfect for a nice brunch with friends and family, spinach pancakes are healthy and can go with any dish served for lunch, breakfast, or dinner. Spinach pancakes are wholesome and completely guilt-free. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Add all the ingredients to your blender and process on high speed until pureed. Step 2 Heat your non-stick cooking pan to medium heat and pour the batter directly from your blender spout to make pancakes that are approx. 4 inches in diameter.Â  And let it cook until several bubbles appear. Step 3 Flip and cook for 4 minutes until golden brown and cooked through. Step 4 Serve with pancake or maple syrup, and fresh avocado and tomatoes. Enjoy! With a cup of coffee.